Description: Probabilistic Logic Networks reasoning engine (runtime)
 PLN (Probabilistic Logic Networks) is a reasoning engine for uncertain
 inference in the OpenCog cognitive architecture. It combines logic and
 probability theory to enable reasoning under uncertainty.
 .
 This package contains the shared libraries for runtime use.

Package: libpln-dev
Section: libdevel
Architecture: any
Depends: libpln (= ${binary:Version}),
         libatomspace-dev (>= 1.0.0),
         libcogutil-dev (>= 1.0.0),
         guile-3.0-dev,
         ${misc:Depends}
Description: Probabilistic Logic Networks reasoning engine (development files)
 PLN (Probabilistic Logic Networks) is a reasoning engine for uncertain
 inference in the OpenCog cognitive architecture. It combines logic and
 probability theory to enable reasoning under uncertainty.
 .
 This package contains the header files and development libraries needed
 for building applications with PLN.
